<div class="homepage-container no-nav">
	<h1 class="text-center">Project 144</h1>
	<div class="row">        
		<div class="col-md-6 offset-md-3">
			<div class="intro text-center">
				<p>Project 144 is a site built specifically for people who enjoy collecting and writing about music, and maybe seeing an opinion or two from someone else. Think of it as "semi-social" media.</p>
				<p>Like all social media, however, peoples' opinions might still make you mad here, but rest easy: in this case, we're letting you know up front that everything is <em>entirely</em> subjective.</p>
			</div>
			<br>
			<form id="signupForm">
				<fieldset>
					<h2 class="text-center">Sign up.  It's free!</h2>
					<div id="fgSignupEmail" class="form-group">
						<label for="signupEmail">Email address</label>
						<input required type="email" class="form-control" id="signupEmail" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter email">
						<div id="badSignupEmail" class="invalid-feedback">That email address is already being used.</div>
					</div>
					<div id="fgSignupUsername" class="form-group">
						<label for="signupUsername">Desired Username</label>
						<input required type="text" class="form-control" id="signupUsername" aria-describedby="username" placeholder="Username">
						<div id="badSignupUsername" class="invalid-feedback"></div>
					</div>
					<div id="fgSignupPassword" class="form-group">
						<label class="form-control-label" for="signupPassword">Password</label>
						<input required type="password" class="form-control" id="signupPassword" placeholder="Password">
						<div id="badSignupPassword" class="invalid-feedback">Your password must be 8-16 characters in length.</div>
					</div>
					<div class="text-center">
						<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Join the Project</button><br><br>
						<p><a href="/login">I already have an account.</a><br>
						- OR -<br>
						<a href="/forgot" class="pull-right">I forgot my password.</a></p>
					</div>
				</fieldset>
			</form>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>